# Create database:

$ sudo aideinit
(this may take some time...)

The general configuration file for AIDE is located under /etc/default/aide.
The rules and configurations resides under /etc/aide/ and the AIDE database is located under /var/lib/aide/.

$ sudo cp /var/lib/aide/aide.db{.new,}

$ sudo update-aide.conf

$ sudo cp /var/lib/aide/aide.conf.autogenerated /etc/aide/aide.conf

$ sudo aide -c /etc/aide/aide.conf -C

NOTE: Whenever you make any AIDE configuration changes, remember to initialize the database to create a baseline.

$ sudo aide -c /home/koromicha/aide/aide.conf -i
